  <h1>
   font_exists
  </h1>
  This function returns whether a font with the specified index exists or not. You can check font indices as defined from the Asset Browser, or fonts that have been added using functions like
  <span>
   font_add()
  </span>
  .
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">font_exists(ind);
</code></pre>
  <table>
   <tbody>
    <tr>
     <th>
      Argument
     </th>
     <th>
      Type
     </th>
     <th>
      Description
     </th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      ind
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../../The_Asset_Editors/Fonts.htm">
        Font Asset
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      Index of the font to check.
     </td>
    </tr>
   </tbody>
  </table>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml"><a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
 Boolean
</a></code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">if font_exists(fnt_Main)
{
    draw_set_font(fnt_Main);
}
</code></pre>
  This will set the active drawing font to
  <span>
   fnt_Main
  </span>
  if it exists.
 </body>
